Comment:
5min in and this movie broadcasts mediocre, made for TV. or straight to DVD. 

I was really hoping for a dark, haunting examination into the birth and mind of a serial killer and the evolution of Leatherface's psyche, but instead we get a dull, comical, cheap and generic directorial style; every scene feels like actors "trying" to act, instead of really inhabiting their rolls and creating that suspension of disbelief that made TCM the cult classic it is. 
There are so many pointless, abrupt close ups of people faces, it's as if the director's only experience is with TV soap operas.

I liked how they kept his secret in the movie and tried to make you guess who it was until the end. I thought it was bud but whom it turns out to be is who you never expected a little spoiler there but not to bad. The only two actors in this movie I knew were Stephen Dorff who plays Texas Ranger Hal Hartman he also played Decan Frost in Blade and Finn Jones who plays a deputy and he is known for his role as Iron Fist. Stephen does a great job and so does Sam Trike who plays Leatherface. The acting, story, directing and makeup effects are great in this movie. If you have not seen this movie then I recommend you do this movie is Cinematastic rating 5/5
